<paragraph role="heading" id="hd_id3149798" xml-lang="en-US" level="1" l10n="U" oldref="1"><variable id="chart_barformat"><link href="text/shared/guide/chart_barformat.xhp" name="Adding Texture to Chart Bars">Adding Texture to Chart Bars</link>
</variable></paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3156136" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="3">You can add texture to the bars in a graph or chart (instead of the default colors) via bitmap graphics:</paragraph>
<list type="ordered">
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3153748" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="4">Enter edit mode by double-clicking on the chart.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3149182" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="5">Double-click on the bar you want to edit. All bars of this series are now selected.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3147275" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="6">In the context menu choose <emph>Object Properties</emph>. Then choose the <emph>Area</emph> tab.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3146797" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="7">Click on <emph>Bitmap</emph>. In the list box select a bitmap as a texture for the currently selected bars. Click <emph>OK</emph> to accept the setting.</paragraph>
</listitem>
</list>
